                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Employer Cost",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "The employer's cost is 23.5% of the employee's salary."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "nested_list",
                        "data": [
                            {
                                "text": "Social Insurance - 17%"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "Health Insurance - 3%"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "Accident Insurance - 0.5%"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "Control Union Fee - 2%"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "Unemployment Insurance - 1%"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Overtime Pay & Maximum Hours",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Standard working hours are 8 hours per day, 40 hours per week. The standard workweek is from Monday to Friday."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Overtime payment is mandatory. Hours outside of standard work hours are considered overtime. Employees can work no more than 12 hours a day, including normal and overtime hours. For overtime hours, employees are paid:"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "nested_list",
                        "data": [
                            {
                                "text": "150% of the hourly rate on weekdays"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "200% of the hourly rate on weekly days off"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "300% of the hourly rate on public holidays"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "Leave Policy": [
            {
                "title": "Maternity Leave",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "Pregnant employees who have contributed to social security for at least 3 months are entitled to 6 months of paid leave. 2 weeks of leave can be taken before the child's birth. The employee will receive 100% of the average salary based on social insurance contributions over the last 6 months. Social Security will be responsible for this pay."
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Paternity Leave",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Employees who have contributed to social security for at least 3 months are entitled to 5 days of paid paternity leave. The employee will receive 100% of the salary during this period, and Social Security will be responsible for this pay."
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Parental Leave",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "In Vietnam, no law covers parental leave. However, employees may be entitled to maternity leave and paternity leave."
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Sick Leave",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "Employees are entitled to paid sick leave for up 30 days. The employee will receive 75% of their salary while on leave paid by Social Security. Leave can be extended depending on the employee, but an extension is done on a case by case basis."
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "Termination": [
            {
                "title": "Termination Requirements",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Terminations must respect complex rules and the rules of an employee’s employment country. The off-boarding is always handled by the Employer with the primary stakeholders. It may include ad-hoc fees as well as required or recommended steps on specific termination cases."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Terminations in Vietnam can be complex. There is no at-will termination in Vietnam for employers outside the probation period and termination must be done for just cause."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Compliant terminations include:"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "nested_list",
                        "data": [
                            {
                                "text": "Voluntarily by the employee"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "By mutual agreement"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "Unilaterally by the employer based on:",
                                "children": [
                                    {
                                        "text": "probation period"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "text": "objective grounds"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "text": "disciplinary dismissal"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "text": "performance due to unsuitability for the job"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "By the expiration of the contract"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Notice Period",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "The minimum notice period is 3 days and will be increased according to the type of contract."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "nested_list",
                        "data": [
                            {
                                "text": "45 days if the contract is indefinite"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "30 days if the contract is fixed term of 12 - 36 months"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "3 working days if the contact is a fixed term under 12 months"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Severance for Employees",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "In Vietnam, all employees who have worked for over a year and are terminated are entitled to severance pay, unless they are terminated for:"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "nested_list",
                        "data": [
                            {
                                "text": "Having committed acts of theft, embezzlement, disclosure of technological and business secrets, or other acts causing severe loss to the property and interests of the enterprise."
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "Having been transferred to another job as a disciplinary measure, the employee then again commits the same breach of labor discipline when the disciplinary measure is still in effect."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Severance pay is half a month of salary per year of service. There is no law capping the amount of severance that can be paid."
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "Statutory time off": [
            {
                "title": "Paid Time Off",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "Both full-time and part-time employees are entitled to 12 working days of paid time off (PTO) a year. PTO accrues monthly at 1 day per month. For every five years working for an employer, the annual leave increases by 1 day."
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Public Holidays",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Vietnam celebrates 6 national holidays (11 days total) and some regional holidays based on the location of the employee. National public holidays include:"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "New Year’s Day: 1 day\nLunar New Year: 5 days\nHung King’s Festival: 1 day\nReunification Day: 1 day\nLabour Day: 1 day\nIndependence Day: 2 days"
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "Onboarding": [
            {
                "title": "Onboarding",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "Onboarding takes"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "3 business days"
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "Additional info": [
            {
                "title": "Employment Contract Details",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Contracts can be written in English. They must be in writing and signed by both parties."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "A contract must include:"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "nested_list",
                        "data": [
                            {
                                "text": "name"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "start date"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "length of the employment"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "job description"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "termination conditions"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Probation Period",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Probation periods are mandatory. The minimum probation period is 6 days and the maximum probation period is 180 days. Probation periods vary depending on the job type."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "table",
                        "data": [
                            {
                                "Job Type": "Managerial Position*",
                                "Probation Period Length (days)": "180"
                            },
                            {
                                "Job Type": "Junior College Degree",
                                "Probation Period Length (days)": "60"
                            },
                            {
                                "Job Type": "Skilled Employees",
                                "Probation Period Length (days)": "30"
                            },
                            {
                                "Job Type": "Other",
                                "Probation Period Length (days)": "6"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "*The legal department must usually approve contracts with 180 days of the probation period before the agreement with the employee."
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
